Package: quant2dist
Title: Fit Parametric Distributions to Reported Quantile Data
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Kim", "Rand", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "kim@mathsinhealth.com"),
    person("Maths in Health", role = "cph"))
Description: Recovers parametric distribution parameters from summary
    statistics (quantiles, means, standard deviations) commonly reported
    in medical and scientific literature. Fits normal, lognormal,
    exponential, beta, gamma, Weibull, and Power Normal distributions
    using maximum likelihood estimation. Selects the best-fitting
    distribution by AIC, BIC, or log-likelihood. Optionally creates
    interactive visualisations of density curves, cumulative probability
    curves, and parameter comparison tables via the 'plotly' package.
